{
  "id": 5149766073843712,
  "name": "Implement CSS property font-language-override",
  "summary": "This feature introduces support for the font-language-override CSS property in Chromium. The property allows developers to override the system language used for OpenType glyph substitution by specifying a four-character language tag directly in CSS.\n\nThis enables fine-grained typographic control, particularly useful for multilingual content or fonts with language-specific glyph variants.",
